# Huellitas Mobile — Cursor Rules

## Stack
React Native + Expo SDK 55, Expo Router v5, TypeScript strict mode, Zustand v5, TanStack Query v5, Better Auth, Zod.

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (PetCard, AlertMarker)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (usePets, useLocation)
- Stores: camelCase with `Store` suffix (authStore, locationStore)
- Services: camelCase with `Service` suffix (pets.service.ts)
- Types: PascalCase with descriptive suffix (PetFormPayload, ApiResponse)
- Files: kebab-case for non-components (api.types.ts, date.utils.ts)
- Expo Router files: kebab-case (sign-in.tsx, [id].tsx)

## File Organization
- Max 400 lines per file. Extract to smaller files if exceeded.
- Group by feature: components/pets/, components/reports/, components/map/
- Co-locate test files: PetCard.tsx → PetCard.test.tsx OR __tests__/PetCard.test.tsx

## Component Rules
- Functional components only (no class components)
- One component per file
- Props interface must be defined above component
- Export named component (not default where possible, but Expo Router screens require default)
- Keep components under 150 lines; extract sub-components otherwise

## State Management
- Zustand for client-side global state (auth, location, settings)
- TanStack Query for server state (API data, caching, polling)
- Do NOT store server data in Zustand (duplication)
- Always use `set(state => ({ ...state, field: value }))` for immutable updates

## Immutability (CRITICAL)
- Never mutate state directly
- Always return new objects: `set(state => ({ ...state, newField: value }))`
- Never push to arrays: use `[...array, newItem]`
- Never modify objects in place: use `{ ...obj, field: newValue }`

## TypeScript
- Enable strict mode (tsconfig.json)
- No implicit `any`
- Define explicit return types for all functions
- Use `unknown` instead of `any` for error types
- Prefer interfaces for component props, types for API payloads

## Expo Router
- File-based routing: screens live in `app/` directory
- Use route groups: (auth) for unauthenticated, (app) for authenticated
- Dynamic routes: `[id].tsx`
- Nested routes: `reports/[id]/sightings/new.tsx`
- Use `useLocalSearchParams()` for route params
- Use `router.push()`, `router.replace()`, `router.back()` for navigation

## Data Fetching
- Use TanStack Query for ALL API calls (no raw axios calls in components)
- Custom hooks wrap `useQuery` and `useMutation`
- Set `staleTime: 30000` for polling data (lost reports)
- Always handle `isLoading`, `isError`, `data` states

## Error Handling
- NEVER swallow errors silently (no empty catch blocks)
- Always log errors: `console.error('context:', error)` or Sentry
- Show user-friendly messages (not raw error.message in UI)
- Use Error Boundaries for component crashes
- Handle network errors gracefully with retry options

## Testing (MANDATORY)
- Write tests BEFORE implementation (TDD)
- Test file naming: ComponentName.test.tsx
- Test coverage: 80% minimum
- Always test: render, user interactions, error states, loading states
- Mock external services (expo-location, expo-notifications, API calls)
- Use @testing-library/react-native

## Security
- Never log sensitive data (tokens, passwords, emails in plain text)
- Use SecureStore (not AsyncStorage) for tokens
- Validate all user inputs with Zod before API calls
- Never trust API responses (validate with Zod schemas)

## Common Anti-Patterns to AVOID
- Prop drilling more than 2 levels deep (use Zustand or Context)
- useEffect with missing dependencies
- Inline styles (use StyleSheet.create)
- Direct database calls from components (use services layer)
- Hardcoded strings (use i18n keys or constants)
- Magic numbers (use named constants)
